## The quality bar for UI and animation

**Perception is the test.** Screenshots and visual checks are the primary
verification. Numerical instrumentation is a tool to diagnose perceptible
problems — never the goal itself.

If a screenshot looks fine but instrumentation shows a 2px residual, ship it.
Chasing pixel-perfect numbers when the perception gap allows shipping is
digital rumination. Do not do it.

When something feels off:
1. Check perception via screenshot first.
2. Instrument only if needed to diagnose.
3. Don't chase numbers if the screenshot is fine.

