## Self-verification for visual changes

After ANY change that touches CSS, animation, ceremony JS, the canvas,
or anything else that affects what the user sees on screen, run a Playwright
screenshot test before declaring the task complete. This catches the failure
mode of "task complete" claims that did not actually land.

Procedure:

1. Identify the relevant state to verify. If the change affects a ceremony
   beat, the test must drive the page into that beat. If the change affects
   an idle visual, a single screenshot of the loaded page is enough. If
   unsure, ask the operator.

2. Write a small Playwright script in `.windsurf-tmp/check.js` (create the
   directory if it doesn't exist; do NOT commit it) that:
   - Loads `atheneum.html` from a local `file://` URL.
   - Drives the page into the relevant state via `window.atheneum.*` dev
     APIs OR by clicking dev-panel buttons OR by direct DOM evaluation.
   - Captures a screenshot to `.windsurf-tmp/after.png`.
   - Optionally: also captures DOM state of the affected elements (computed
     styles, class names, opacity) and prints them.

3. Run the script. If it errors, fix the issue and rerun. If it succeeds,
   view the screenshot and confirm by inspection that the change matches
   what the operator asked for.

4. Report back to the operator with:
   - The screenshot path so the operator can view it.
   - A one-sentence description of what was observed.
   - The line `Visual check: PASS` or `Visual check: FAIL — <reason>`.
   - If FAIL, do not declare the task complete. Investigate the root cause
     and propose the next step instead.

Skip self-verification only when:
- The change is purely a code rename, comment edit, or other zero-visual-
  impact change. In this case, state explicitly: "Skipping self-verification:
  zero visual surface."
- The operator explicitly says "skip verification" in the instruction.

If Playwright is not available in the environment (no `@playwright/test` in
`node_modules`, no `playwright` binary on PATH), report this to the operator
and ask whether to install it or to proceed without verification. Do NOT
silently skip.

The `.windsurf-tmp/` directory should be added to `.gitignore` if it is not
already. Verification artifacts are scratch work, not source.

