## Voice and brand (when touching user-facing copy)

Register: **manuscript-celestial. Temple not carnival.** Reverent, precise,
mythic. Not playful, not casual, not tech-bro.

Reserved capitalized terms — treat with care, do not rename, do not lowercase:
**Path, Vantage, Gap, Engine, Interpreter, Capacity, Vitality, Spirit,
Alignment, Atheneum, Scriptorium, Reliquary, Codex, Essence, Pool, Thread.**

Body copy register:
- Crimson Pro italic for invitation/manuscript text.
- Sentences short, declarative, often without articles.
- Never exclamatory.
- "Your path is open" — good. "Let's get started" — wrong register.

Writing rules to enforce when editing copy:
1. No self-validating transitions. ("Here is what closes this section" — cut.)
2. No fake-alternative emphasis. No "real, actually, genuinely, truly" doing
   contrast work.
3. No pre-defending against objections the reader didn't make.
4. No guru voice. Wise elder, not guru.
5. One idea per sentence at turning points.

